body.description: No job is too big, no pup is too small! Luvs diapers with new Paw Patrol designs have your back—and their butts. Luvs now has up to 12 hours of protection, day and night. Like Chase and Marshall would say, our highly trained paws are at your service. And diaper leaks? We’re on the case with nonstop leak protection. Luvs Triple Leakguards absorb quickly to help stop diaper leaks before they happen. But our leak protection doesn’t stop there. Secure cuffs and stretchy sides keep leaks locked in where they happen the most. Forget about cheap, leaky diapers and spend more time enjoying this ride known as parenting. With Luvs you know when they go, thanks to a wetness indicator that turns blue on contact with wetness. You care what your baby wears, so Luvs diapers are 100% hypoallergenic, made free of parabens and free of latex* (*natural rubber). When it comes to the ultimate diaper protection, these paws uphold the laws. Our diapers are so good, you don’t need this, but Luvs does offer a money-back guarantee. If you aren’t fully loving your Luvs diapers, we will gladly send you a refund. See luvsdiapers.com for terms and conditions.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works for fur babies too
reviews.reviewText: I need to find a way to keep my fur baby dry now that he is getting up there in years . I found dog diapers on amazon and they looked just like reg baby diapers but worn like a skirt instead of how you put it on a baby . I figured for the price I’d be better off buying these in sz 4 and they worked so well !! They keep my lil dude dry and he can walk around without any issues. It’s so much better than using puppy pads for him to lay on . These work great on my 12 lb dog . I think a sz 5 would work too . He’s built like a little tank . These have the line on them that let me know when he is wet . They smell really good too ! I used these for my kids when they were babies . Still great quality for a great price . I’m super happy with how well they absorb pee . My little old man dog was stinky and needed a bath daily when I was using puppy pads under him to keep him dry but it was not working very well . These keep him dry and he’s not stinky like he’s making Jenkum . Now I can use just the diaper and a fabric Welping pad to keep him comfortable, clean and dry . It’s his golden years right now and quality of life is the most important factor right now . I think it’s cute that my dog is wearing his little diaper wrap that has a bunch of dogs printed on it (paw patrol ) . In my experience these work great on both fur babies and real babies !

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Honestly these are the best value diaper in my opinion. They do great overnight which is super surprising since they are not overnight diapers! I haven’t had a problem since switching to them at all! The price point is great for a mom who has two kids in diapers! Quality is great for the price too! Never disappointed. No rashes at all!

reviews.reviewText: I am 42 years old and have a 25 year old & 20 year old. I used this brand of diapers on them when they were babies. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not for heavy wetters
reviews.reviewText: Doesn’t absorb properly. Depending on your little ones position the urine will accumulate all in one area causing problems like- urine to remain on their skin, disfigured diaper, leakage, accumulation of urine in the front of the pamper (tummy time) will cause their shirt to absorb the urine, the pampers cause the gel to magically come out in the pamper on your baby’s sensitive areas. I’m not a fan… each kid is different so this pamper may work for yours but it doesn’t work for mine. They did work good for my first kid who was a light wetter but not perfectly.
